Two minor points:

First, I think it would be nice if we east coast NSF people didn't
have to go to California or the MILnet to do a host lookup.  I don't
know what the effect of putting a name server on the NSFnet but it
sure couldn't hurt.

Last, what effect does increasing the lifetimes of cache entries on
local named's have on load?  Is there any reason not to expire entries
for periods as long as a week or more?  After all, when was the last
time you changed your host address?
-- 
Eliot Lear
[lear@rutgers.edu]

